title: Missy Franklin
summary: Melissa Jeanette Franklin (born May 10, 1995) is an American former competition swimmer and five-time Olympic gold medalist. She formerly held the world record in the 200-meter backstroke (long course).[2][3] As a member of the U.S. national swim team, she also held the world records in the 4Ã—100-meter medley relay (short course and long course).[4]
